    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The MolNetEnhancer workflow results in one graphml network file that contains all the structural information obtained from the individual tools. Such a file can be easily imported into network visualization tools such as Cytoscape [31], an environment where additional metadata on the molecular features can be added. In addition, all structural information is also available as tab delimited text files.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes output as graphml files containing integrated structural information including Mass2Motifs, which can be visualized in Cytoscape.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo9070144",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Annotated molecular network file with embedded Mass2Motif substructural information mapped to network nodes",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:37:32.998044+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card specifies 'classical-mode' GNPS networks, which is accurate\u2014the paper explicitly discusses both classical (MS-Cluster based) and feature-based (MZmine2) molecular networking modes, and case studies 3 & 4 demonstrate classical-mode application.",
        "The card focuses narrowly on the MS2LDA-to-network mapping component, which is one of two main integration steps in MolNetEnhancer (the other being chemical class annotation via ClassyFire). This is a valid sub-task within the broader workflow."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 2,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:37:32.998044+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The workflow enhances the currently available molecular networking methods based on either MS-Cluster [29] (classical) or MZmine2 [30] (also called \"feature-based molecular networking\") and results in annotated molecular networks that can be explored in Cytoscape [31]... Substructural information retrieved through MS2LDA is integrated in two ways within the mass spectral molecular networks. Shared substructures or motifs between two molecular features are visualized as multiple edges connecting the nodes. Furthermore, motifs found within a molecular feature can be visualized as pie charts, where the relative abundance of each motif represents the overlap score, a score measuring how much of the motif is present in the spectrum [32].",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes mapping MS2LDA substructural motifs (Mass2Motifs) onto feature-based molecular networks from GNPS.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo9070144",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does the feature-based mode pipeline map Mass2Motif substructural information from MS2LDA onto a GNPS feature-based molecular network?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:37:50.422711+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MolNetEnhancer is freely available on GitHub at https://github.com/madeleineernst/pyMolNetEnhancer and https://github.com/madeleineernst/RMolNetEnhancer.",
      "asbval:note": "The Python implementation of MolNetEnhancer is explicitly named and referenced.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo9070144",
