      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The workflow enhances the currently available molecular networking methods based on either MS-Cluster [29] (classical) or MZmine2 [30] (also called \"feature-based molecular networking\") and results in annotated molecular networks that can be explored in Cytoscape [31]... Substructural information retrieved through MS2LDA is integrated in two ways within the mass spectral molecular networks. Shared substructures or motifs between two molecular features are visualized as multiple edges connecting the nodes. Furthermore, motifs found within a molecular feature can be visualized as pie charts, where the relative abundance of each motif represents the overlap score, a score measuring how much of the motif is present in the spectrum [32].",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes the output as annotated molecular networks with MS2LDA motif information integrated and visualized on nodes and edges.",
