      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The MolNetEnhancer workflow results in one graphml network file that contains all the structural information obtained from the individual tools. Such a file can be easily imported into network visualization tools such as Cytoscape [31]... To retrieve the most abundant chemical classes per molecular family, all chemical structures obtained through GNPS library matching, and in silico chemical structural annotation are submitted to automated chemical classification",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes enriching networks with chemical class information, but emphasizes that this comes from BOTH GNPS library matching AND in silico annotation tools (NAP, DEREPLICATOR, SIRIUS+CSI:FingerID), not GNPS library matches alone. The card's scope is narrower than the actual capability.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo9070144",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chemical-class-node-mapping",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope - When to use",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You have a GNPS mass spectral molecular network (in graphml or cytoscape format) and want to enrich its nodes with chemical class information derived from GNPS public library spectral matches.",
