      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Substructural information retrieved through MS2LDA is integrated in two ways within the mass spectral molecular networks... Furthermore, for each molecular family, the x most shared motifs are shown, where x is defined by the user... To retrieve the most abundant chemical classes per molecular family, all chemical structures obtained through GNPS library matching, and in silico chemical structural annotation are submitted to automated chemical classification",
      "asbval:note": "The paper clearly distinguishes between MS2LDA motif mapping and chemical class mapping as two separate steps in MolNetEnhancer, supporting the distinction made in the card.",
